In this article, President Trump addresses the devastation caused by hurricanes in Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands, stating that the government is working to provide assistance and support for recovery efforts. He also discusses his recent announcement of tax reform, highlighting four key ideas: cutting taxes for working families, simplifying the tax code, restoring America's competitive edge, and encouraging the repatriation of wealth held overseas. He emphasizes the importance of passing tax reform to create jobs, boost the economy, and fulfill the American Dream. However, he criticizes Democrats for not supporting tax cuts and argues that raising taxes would negatively impact the country. The President concludes by expressing his belief that this tax reform will be the largest in the nation's history.